Let $p$ be a prime number, let $\Gamma$ be a pro-$p$ group with a hereditarily linearly increasing rank, let $H$ be a finitely generated subgroup of $\Gamma$, and let $K$ be an open subgroup of $H$. Then $\sqrt{H} = \sqrt{K}$.

\end{proposition}

\begin{proof}

Since $K \leq_o H$ we have $H \leq_o \sqrt{K}$ so $\sqrt{K} \leq_o \sqrt{H}$. On the other hand, $K \leq_o H \leq_o \sqrt{H}$ so $K \leq_o \sqrt{H}$ and thus $\sqrt{H} \leq_o \sqrt{K}$.

\end{proof}

